RESIDENTS have been urged to stay inside in case of potentially toxic fumes from a fire at a recycling centre.
 Fire crews were called to the scene in Henderson Drive, Inverness, at around 6pm this evening. 
 The Scottish Fire and Rescue Service sent four appliances to deal with the incident. 
 
 
Fire Inverness Transfer Centre earlier https://t.co/v6BIGK500v

Police urged nearby residents to close all windows and doors and keep themselves and any pets indoors as fire crews control the fire, due to smoke and potentially toxic fumes from the fire. 
There are no reports of any injuries.
